<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - FRONT COVER, VIBRATION DAMPER, and GEROTOR OIL PUMP -
        Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s26505.4">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc id="s26505.4.1" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="5">
            <title>Front Cover</title>
            <figure id="f2650522" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D0625.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Front cover crankcase dowels</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If removed, install front cover crankcase dowels.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Dowels may become lodged in front cover. Remove dowels and install in crankcase, if
                        necessary.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f2650523" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D0628A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Liquid gasket applications</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply Liquid Gasket (RTV) to joining surfaces of crankcase and lower crankcase.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Install gasket and cover within five minutes before the liquid gasket forms a skin to ensure a
                        leak proof joint.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f2650524" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D0626A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Front cover gasket installed</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position a new front cover gasket on the crankcase.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650525" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D0631A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Front cover alignment</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Alignment guides</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align front cover with crankcase dowels and alignment guides (made locally).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650526" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd05/D0501D.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Front cover module retaining bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Fasten front cover assembly to crankcase with 16 bolts (M8 x 35 hex flanged, dog point).
                    Tighten bolts to the special torque .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If removed, install water pump on front cover with new O-ring. See .</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
